<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Bates, H. W." box="[431,576,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" refId="ref10917" refString="Bates, H. W. (1880) Longicornia. In: Godman, F. D. &amp; Salvin, O. (Eds.), Biologia Centrali-Americana, Insecta, Coleoptera. Vol. 5. Taylor and Francis, London, pp. 17 - 152." type="book" year="1880">Bates (1880)</bibRefCitation>
on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1868" box="[620,737,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oxycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[620,737,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Oxycoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: “A curious genus of the 
<emphasis box="[1028,1159,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Molorchina</emphasis>
group, with abbreviated triangular elytra. It is allied to the European and North-American 
<taxonomicName box="[891,1017,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Callimoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[891,1017,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Callimoxys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is scarcely distinguishable from 
<emphasis box="[151,274,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Merioneda</emphasis>
[sic] (Pascoe) of the Malay Archipelago and 
<collectingCountry box="[767,866,223,249]" name="Malaysia" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Malacca</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bates)" baseAuthorityName="Bates" box="[874,1107,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Stenoptrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[874,1021,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Stenoptrellus</emphasis>
(Bates)
</taxonomicName>
from the Amazons, published a year after 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1868" box="[281,398,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oxycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[281,398,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Oxycoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is evidently congeneric.” Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bates, H. W." box="[764,907,258,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" refId="ref10969" refString="Bates, H. W. (1885) Supplement to Longicornia. In: Godman, F. D. &amp; Salvin, O. (Eds.), Biologia Centrali-Americana, Insecta, Coleoptera. Vol. 5. Taylor and Francis, London, pp. 249 - 436." type="book" year="1885">Bates (1885)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1868" box="[1068,1185,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oxycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1068,1185,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Oxycoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1858" box="[1246,1383,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Merionoeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1246,1383,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Merionoeda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and reported: “The structural characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1858" box="[591,728,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Merionoeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[591,728,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Merionoeda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1868" box="[784,901,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oxycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[784,901,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Oxycoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in both sexes offer no essential difference: and united they form a well-marked and most interesting genus, allied to the European and North-American genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Callimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Callimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.” 
<bibRefCitation author="Chemsak, J. A. &amp; Linsley, E. G." box="[222,527,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" pagination="181 - 184" refId="ref11193" refString="Chemsak, J. A. &amp; Linsley, E. G. (1974) Reclassification, synonymy, and descriptions of some North and Central American Cerambycidae (Coleoptera). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 28 (4), 181 - 184." type="journal article" year="1974">Chemsak &amp; Linsley (1974)</bibRefCitation>
, without explanation, transferred 
<taxonomicName authority="(Melzer, 1934)" baseAuthorityName="Melzer" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[901,1299,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Merionoeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[901,1125,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Merionoeda bicolor</emphasis>
(Melzer, 1934)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bates, 1870)" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1870" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Merionoeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="culicina">
<emphasis box="[1310,1436,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">M. culicina</emphasis>
(Bates, 1870)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bates, 1885" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1885" box="[317,590,402,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Merionoeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gratiosa">
<emphasis box="[317,447,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">M. gratiosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bates, H. W." box="[455,590,402,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" refId="ref10969" refString="Bates, H. W. (1885) Supplement to Longicornia. In: Godman, F. D. &amp; Salvin, O. (Eds.), Biologia Centrali-Americana, Insecta, Coleoptera. Vol. 5. Taylor and Francis, London, pp. 249 - 436." type="book" year="1885">Bates, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lacordaire, 1868)" baseAuthorityName="Lacordaire" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[649,996,403,430]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Merionoeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavipes">
<emphasis box="[649,779,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">M. clavipes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lacordaire, J. T." box="[793,988,403,430]" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" refId="ref11483" refString="Lacordaire, J. T. (1868) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Genera des Coleopteres, ou expose methodique et critique de tous les genres proposes jusqu'ici dans cet ordre d'insectes. Vol. 8. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, 552 pp." type="book" year="1868">Lacordaire, 1868</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1868" box="[1032,1149,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oxycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1149,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Oxycoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Tippmann, 1953" authorityName="Tippmann" authorityYear="1953" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Merionoeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis box="[1163,1436,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Merionoeda brasiliensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tippmann, F. F." box="[151,338,438,465]" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" pagination="181 - 228" refId="ref12447" refString="Tippmann, F. F. (1953) Studien uber neotropische Longicornier I (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae). Dusenia, 4, 181 - 228." type="journal article" year="1953">Tippmann, 1953</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zajciw, 1964" authorityName="Zajciw" authorityYear="1964" box="[349,811,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Merionoeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatipennis">
<emphasis box="[349,655,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Merionoeda carinatipennis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zajciw, D." box="[662,811,439,465]" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" pagination="247 - 256" refId="ref12643" refString="Zajciw, D. (1964) Revisao das especies brasileiras do genero Merionoeda Pascoe (Col., Cerambycidae). Studia Entomologica, 7 (1 - 4), 247 - 256." type="journal article" year="1964">Zajciw, 1964</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Zajciw, 1964" authorityName="Zajciw" authorityYear="1964" box="[869,1267,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Merionoeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficollis">
<emphasis box="[869,1114,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Merionoeda ruficollis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zajciw, D." box="[1121,1267,439,465]" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" pagination="247 - 256" refId="ref12643" refString="Zajciw, D. (1964) Revisao das especies brasileiras do genero Merionoeda Pascoe (Col., Cerambycidae). Studia Entomologica, 7 (1 - 4), 247 - 256." type="journal article" year="1964">Zajciw, 1964</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
were not mentioned. These three species were included in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1868" box="[667,784,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oxycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[667,784,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Oxycoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also without explanation, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A. &amp; Giesbert, E. F." box="[1132,1432,475,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" pagination="249 - 255" refId="ref11998" refString="Monne, M. A. &amp; Giesbert, E. F. (1992) Nomenclatural notes on Western Hemisphere Cerambycidae (Coleoptera). Insecta Mundi, 6 (2), 249 - 255." type="journal article" year="1992">Monné &amp; Giesbert (1992)</bibRefCitation>
. As the transference of the 
<typeStatus box="[456,504,511,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1868" box="[635,752,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oxycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[635,752,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Oxycoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lacordaire" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[770,898,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Merionoeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clavipes">
<emphasis box="[770,898,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">O. clavipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) occurred in 
<bibRefCitation author="Chemsak, J. A. &amp; Linsley, E. G." box="[1054,1368,511,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" pagination="181 - 184" refId="ref11193" refString="Chemsak, J. A. &amp; Linsley, E. G. (1974) Reclassification, synonymy, and descriptions of some North and Central American Cerambycidae (Coleoptera). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 28 (4), 181 - 184." type="journal article" year="1974">Chemsak &amp; Linsley (1974)</bibRefCitation>
, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1858" box="[151,288,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Merionoeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,288,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Merionoeda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1868" box="[324,441,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oxycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[324,441,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Oxycoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it must be considered that the revalidation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1868" box="[961,1078,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oxycoleus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[961,1078,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="358">Oxycoleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurred in this work.
</paragraph>
